            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "The tests use are lua scripts executed by [busted](https://github.com/Olivine-Labs/busted). The functional tests in particular use the [lua-client](https://github.com/neovim/lua-client) to start nvim and call the API. I you check test/functional/helpers.lua, those are mostly helper functions build aroud lua-client.\n\nIncidentally if you want this to test plugins, there is also [Vroom](https://github.com/google/vroom) - but I think I just spotted a bug in its Neovim support, probably because API changes in python-client (**Edit:** followup here https://github.com/google/vroom/pull/104).\n",
